						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab set up in the temple of Pāvaḍi Basappa.</hi></p>						

						<p>Trailōkyamalla (Sōmēśvara I)—A.D. 1044.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 966, Tāraṇa, Pushya, śu. 2, Monday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1044, December 24.</hi></p>						

						<p>It refers to a Mahāsāmanta (name lost) who is described as the Lord of <hi rend="bold">Tagaranagara,</hi> as ruling at <hi rend="bold">Eḷamēla</hi> and records a gift of land to the temple of Uttarēśvara It mentions Brahmarāśi.</p>						

						</summary>
